```julia
function clean_column(col::String)
    return strip(lowercase(replace(col, [' ', '-'] => '_')))
end
```

This function takes a string `col` representing a column name and returns the cleaned version. It strips leading and trailing whitespaces using `strip()`, lowercases the entire string using `lowercase()`, and then replaces any spaces or hyphens with an underscore using `replace()`. The result is a string where the column name is in lowercase with underscores instead of spaces or hyphens.
